A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring several cities upon their designation as Georgia PlanFirst communities; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the year 2025 marks the 35th anniversary of the implementation of the Georgia
4 Planning Act, which established that the State of Georgia must maintain an essential public
5 interest in protecting and preserving the natural resources, the environment, and the vital
6 areas of the state as well as serve these interests through coordinated and comprehensive
7 planning by all local governments; and
8 WHEREAS, local governments throughout our state have undertaken the tasks necessary to
9 implement comprehensive plans to protect and enhance the quality of life within their
10 respective communities; and
11 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia recognizes the important role communities play in
12 fostering the state's role as an attractive, inclusive place to invest, conduct business, learn,
13 live, engage in recreation, and raise a family; moreover, planning helps to create a
14 sustainable environment of predictability for economic development, property owners, and
15 all Georgians; and
