16 WHEREAS, it is the wish of this legislative body to recognize and honor those communities
17 that have dedicated their purposeful work to establishing a vision for their future growth and
18 development and have taken the steps necessary to set a path needed to achieve this vision;
19 and
20 WHEREAS, the Georgia Department of Community Affairs acknowledges the importance
21 of coordinated and comprehensive planning to the state; therefore, the PlanFirst program has
22 been created to recognize those communities in Georgia that have shown an exemplary
23 history of comprehensive plan development and implementation; and
24 WHEREAS, this legislative body is justly proud to honor the City of Acworth, the City of
25 Alma, the City of Augusta, the City of Camilla, the City of Griffin, the City of Monroe, the
26 City of Toccoa, and the City of Warner Robins for their outstanding and commendable
27 community planning efforts and accomplishments, which hereby designate them as Georgia
28 PlanFirst communities; and
29 WHEREAS, it is the sense of this legislative body that those local governments that enhance
30 the well-being and vitality of their communities and have shown a long and sustained
31 commitment to excellence in planning and plan implementation certainly have earned the
32 recognition and applause of all the citizens of this great state.
33 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
34 the members of this body honor the City of Acworth, the City of Alma, the City of Augusta,
35 the City of Camilla, the City of Griffin, the City of Monroe, the City of Toccoa, and the City
36 of Warner Robins for their many community planning accomplishments in conjunction with
37 the 35th anniversary of the Georgia Planning Act.
